    <id>https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/boston-beans</id>
    <title>Boston beans</title>
    <updated>2026-03-14T18:22:59.097396+00:00</updated>
    <content type="html">&lt;h1 style="text-align:center;font-family:sans-serif;"&gt;Boston beans&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;img src="https://www.strangerfoods.org/images/boston-beans.webp" style="text-align:center;"/&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;p style="font-family:sans-serif;&gt;You may notice I’ve removed the word ‘baked’ from this recipe title. These beans are cooked on the hob, with no overnight soaking nor long, slow cooking in the oven, so they’re perfect when you’re short on time.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/boston-beans"/>
    <published>2026-02-28T00:00:00+00:00</published>
