    <id>https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/yogurtlu-kebap-with-hot-spiced-butter</id>
    <title>Yogurtlu kebap with hot spiced butter</title>
    <updated>2026-03-14T18:22:59.096693+00:00</updated>
    <content type="html">&lt;h1 style="text-align:center;font-family:sans-serif;"&gt;Yogurtlu kebap with hot spiced butter&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;img src="https://www.strangerfoods.org/images/yogurtlu-kebap-with-hot-spiced-butter.webp" style="text-align:center;"/&gt;
        &lt;br&gt;
        &lt;p style="font-family:sans-serif;&gt;From the Iskender kebabs of Bursa to the Beyti kebabs of Istanbul, there are a whole variety of fabulous Turkish kebabs to choose from. But here we have one of our favourites - yogurtlu kofte kebap! These kebabs consist of fried pitta bread topped with juicy lamb kofta, a simple tomato sauce, a drizzle of yoghurt and finely hot spiced butter on top. It's a rich and delicious combination served with a simple salad and some chips or rice on the side. &lt;/p&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://www.strangerfoods.org/recipes/yogurtlu-kebap-with-hot-spiced-butter"/>
    <published>2026-03-08T00:00:00+00:00</published>
    <media:group>
      <media:thumbnail url="https://www.strangerfoods.org/images/yogurtlu-kebap-with-hot-spiced-butter.webp" height="288" width="512" time="0"/>
    </media:group>
